race.comment: BUNDELLA (3) has a win and a second from two starts over this course and distance and will be rock-hard fit for this. Shapes as one of the major players for this contest. The well-related HEART AND SPIRIT (6) (full to G1 winner Jonker) is a three-time winner here around her home circuit and gets 3kg off with the claim. Can run a big race while fresh. PROVANCE (5) gets Rodd on board from the low draw and looks a must for the exotics players. NEW HAMPSHIRE (4) strips fitter second-up from the break and may earn a cheque with the right run from the inside alley. CUSTO (1) has a ton of weight but will be cherry-ripe and shouldn't be discounted lightly.
